title: Vacant tenements: 283-288 Monroe St - Jackson St, Manhattan
Street view: Monroe St.-Jackson St., Manhattan

text:
Monroe Street, east from and including Jackson to Grand Streets. A portion of Brooklyn appears under the Williamsburg Bridge roadway.

March 23, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.

The 5 story tenement at the left, No. 275 Monroe St., at the N. E. corner of Jackson St., is to be razed according to the N. Y. Sun of March 27, 1939. To the east of same is a 4 story factory (No. 293-7) that is to go also.

Jackson Street, east side, north from Monroe Street, showing several stages of the demolition extending to Madison Street. At the left appears a view of a portion of Grand Street.

Monroe Street, east from Jackson Street, showing a portion of the demolition for the Vladeck City Houses. Four identical structures are to be erected here; two on either side of Monroe Street, at the corners shown. Behind the photographer will rise the companion USHA project, Vladeck Houses. The latter, a government development and the larger of the two, is not to be confused with the forme. For a descriptive article and an architect's drawing, see the New York Times of Nov. 22, 1939.
